data.name: Wee Whistle Stop Cafe
data.full_address: Wee Whistle Stop Cafe, Loch Torridon Community Centre, Torridon, Achnasheen IV22 2EZ, United Kingdom

reviews.review_text: An absolute must-visit in the Loch Torridon area. Some fantastic options for breakfast and lunch, including some stellar cheese toasted sandwiches, lovely cakes and coffees etc. And set with a stunning mountain backdrop and view of Loch Torridon. Don't miss the Deer Museum down the road as well, a short walk from the car park.

translations.en: An absolute must-visit in the Loch Torridon area. Some fantastic options for breakfast and lunch, including some stellar cheese toasted sandwiches, lovely cakes and coffees etc. And set with a stunning mountain backdrop and view of Loch Torridon. Don't miss the Deer Museum down the road as well, a short walk from the car park.

reviews.review_text: 4 in our party and we got here around 10 am. We were seated right away and served promptly! Food was excellent and great coffee too! Prices quite fair. Atmosphere was lovely too!

translations.en: 4 in our party and we got here around 10 am. We were seated right away and served promptly! Food was excellent and great coffee too! Prices quite fair. Atmosphere was lovely too!

reviews.review_text:
I really hope the owners see this review.
We have had a cafe breakfast every morning of our highland trek, and I rarely feel compelled to write a negative review of any establishment. Unfortunately, despite the absolutely delicious food, there was a feeling of hostility the entire visit.

Charges of ¬£1 to charge a phone.
Hidden charge of ¬£1.5 to swap tomatoes for mushrooms on a breakfast. ¬£1.5 to scramble eggs instead of fried.
All this discovered only when we questioned the high price of the bill.
All can simply be avoided by informing us that the changes would have cost extra.

All of the above made us feel like we were being burdensome as customers, and being charged for all our ‚Äònuisances‚Äô.

reviews.review_text:
Rude.
While I specifically asked if it was okay to use my laptop while eating/drinking (they said yes, and happy to pay the ¬£1 to use the power socket), they lied and asked me to leave üòßü§Ø

I put a headset on (after ordering TWO pots of tea, a soft drink, and snacks), where they then told me it wasn't an internet cafe?! I'm utterly shocked. I was not making noise, I specifically asked if they were okay if I used my laptop before I sat down, which they responded fine when I came in...

They were VERY quiet, otherwise I'd of maybe understood and not of left this review.
But as they charged me for a power socket and asked me to leave after one hour and lots of consumables, I'm shocked.
I would NOT return.

No gluten free options, nor dairy alternatives - do not recommend for dietary restrictions ‚ùå
